Defendant Todd Adam Hollfelder in court with attorney Darryl E. Smith.  Defendant Todd Adam Hollfelder in custody.  Jeremy Arn appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Negotiations placed on the record.   Sentencing proceeded. Statements made by State and defense.

As to Count 1:
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of  3.5 years, CONCURRENT to case #15CF713, but CONSECUTIVE with any other time being served with credit for 146 days served. The INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 18 MONTHS.  The MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION IS 2 YEARS.

The defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program but is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program, but only after serving the first 2.5 years of this sentence and the sentence in case #15CF713.

CONDITIONS OF SUPERVISION:
*Obtain AODA assessment and successfully complete follow-up treatment;
*Absolute sobriety with random urine screens and breathalyzer tests;
*No drug dealing or association with drug community (drug users/dealers or drug houses);
*Cooperate with any and all rules set forth by the probation agent;
*No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause;
*Obtain/maintain full time employment or full time school and part time employment;
*Mental health assessment and any follow-up care and/or treatment;
*Participate in any and all programming recommended by the assessing agency or the DOC thinks is appropriate;
*Take all medications in a manner prescribed by a treating physician;
*Provide DNA sample- pay surcharge;
*Pay all applicable mandatory surcharges, fees, assessments, and costs; 
*Fine in the amount of $1,800;
 The Court ordered that all financial obligations and/or restitution be paid through collection of sums by the Department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision.  Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment.


Court ordered Intoxicated Driver Assessment; form filed; copy to defendant.

Court ordered defendant's operating privileges revoked for 36 months with the mandatory reinstatement fee.  

Defendant's operating privilege for operation of Class D vehicles is restricted to operating vehicles that are equipped with an ignition interlock device; and each motor vehicle for which the defendant's name appears on the vehicle's certificate of title or registration must be equipped with an ignition interlock device beginning on the date the department issues any license and for a period of  3 years thereafter.


Appeal rights given. Informed of voting restrictions. 


Filed;
-Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief;
-Pretrial Incarceration Credit;
-Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence.
